{"key":"processedPost-8566019","value":{"id":8566019,"first":8565783,"last":8566753,"when":1214495826,"utime":"06/26/08 06:57 PM","cleanedPost":"If you're going to cover the holes with anything, use window screens.&nbsp; However, gnats shouldn't be a problem if you use normal sanitary procedures, such as not having houseplants nearby.&nbsp; Besides, I've never seen fungus gnats cause much of a problem.&nbsp; They don't eat much, and don't nest in substrates unless someone made one way too wet and the mycelium can't colonize it.&nbsp; In addition, gnats are easy to control.<br />Never cover the holes in a fruiting chamber with tape or polyfil.&nbsp; They only allow gas exchange, and not air exchange which is the number one pinning trigger, and also the number one contamination control.<br />RR"}}